# IQ-ME — per-language reviewer-of-record discipline (FR49, NFR29).
#
# Branch protection (Story 7.8) requires BOTH a maintainer review AND the
# per-language reviewer-of-record review before merging any non-EN content-key
# change. See docs/branch-protection-config.md for the exact main-branch
# settings + the dual-approval / no-bypass enforcement + the synthetic-PR
# regression-recovery playbook. At v0.0.1 the per-language reviewers are
# placeholders pending Gate 9c (RU) and Gate 9d (PL) outreach close.
#
# Format reminder: <pattern> <owner1> <owner2> ...
# Each non-EN path lists BOTH the per-language reviewer-of-record AND the
# maintainer (@Bulrock) as co-owners — this is the dual-approval structure
# (Story 7.8 / FR49). `@TBD-*` handles are intentionally NOT real GitHub
# usernames — they fail CODEOWNERS resolution, which is the signal to
# lint-trust-artifacts.mjs (Story 1.6 / 1.9) that the reviewer-of-record
# is still un-resolved. Do NOT replace these with real handles until the
# corresponding Gate (9c/9d) is documented as closed in CHANGELOG.md.

# Default: project maintainers own the repo.
* @Bulrock

